    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "## Knowledge backlog task\n\nShip one coherent graph update that ties together **Quantum field theory** study notes and draft worldbuilding notes for **The Sword Isles**.\n\n- Confirm links to the assistant persona for retrieval relevance.\n- Assign execution to the user profile returned by `GetUserInitGraph`."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "## Quantum field theory document\n\nThese notes summarize why renormalization in quantum field theory can still produce stable predictions. The central object is the generating functional $Z[J]$ and its connected counterpart $W[J]$."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000003",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "### Derivation snippet\n\nFor the scalar field action, the perturbative expansion tracks powers of the coupling and loop corrections.\n\n$$\n\\mathcal{L} = \\frac{1}{2}(\\partial_\\mu \\phi)(\\partial^\\mu \\phi) - \\frac{1}{2}m^2\\phi^2 - \\frac{\\lambda}{4!}\\phi^4\n$$"
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000004",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "#### Practical interpretation\n\nWhen writing summaries for retrieval, mention that counterterms absorb divergences while observables remain finite. Also keep plain-language intuition beside equations so future assistant responses can cite both narrative and math context."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000005",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "## University context\n\nThe user studied physics at the **University of Duisburg-Essen** and frequently moved between Duisburg and Essen campuses while working with the Faculty of Physics."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000006",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "## Loose life notes\n\n- Morning: reviewed Quantum field theory flash cards.\n- Afternoon: drafted chapter beats for The Sword Isles.\n- Evening: outlined duel choreography for Captain Mirelle Voss in Bristleharbor."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000007",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "## The Sword Isles world note\n\nDraft premise: The Sword Isles is an archipelago of oath-bound ports where reputation travels faster than ships. The first act opens in **Bristleharbor**, where debts and duels shape politics."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000008",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "### Character focus: Captain Mirelle Voss\n\nMirelle is a swashbuckling rogue who treats every negotiation as a measured duel. Her tactical style is to create asymmetry: one feint, one truth, one impossible choice."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000009",
      "type_id": "node.quote",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "> \"Steel is honest. People are where the real gamble begins.\""
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    },
    {
      "id": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000010",
      "type_id": "node.block",
      "properties": [
        {
          "key": "text",
          "string_value": "#### Scene mechanics\n\nIn the harbor duel chapter, embed one symbolic equation in the margin to mirror balancing forces: $\\Delta p \\cdot \\Delta x \\geq \\hbar/2$. Even in fiction notes, this links back to the user's physics voice."
        }
      ],
      "user_id": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
      "visibility": "PRIVATE"
    }
